From: "MEMI>
To:'
Subject: FW: Maxwell - RTC 
Date: Fri, 15 Oct 2021 15:45:30 +0000 
Attachments: Maxwell RTC ell.docx 
Hi guys, 
I'm pretty slammed as we're in the thick of a period where we have 23 briefs due in the span of 30 days, plus the usual 
other appeals stuff going on. I've also never been asked to review an entire RTC like this (neither has Sarah, for what it's 
worth), so I don't think you'll get much value-add anyway. I want to be helpful, of course, but is there something discrete 
and tricky you need help with on these? 
Thanks, 
From: 
Sent: Monday, October 11, 20218:14 PM 
To: 
Cc: 
Subject: RE: Maxwell - RTC 
HIM, 
We just wanted to check in and see if you think you'll have a chance to look at the Maxwell RTC before we send it to the 
defense. We're planning to do that on October 20, and if you have time to look at this before then, we'd really like to 
incorporate your comments. 
Thanks! 
From: 
Sent: Thursday, September 30, 2021 10:50 AM 
To: 
Cc: 
Subject: 
Maxwell - RTC 
Hi=, 
I hope all's well! Attached is a draft of our RTC in the Maxwell case. If you have time to look at it, we'd love any 
comments you might have. 
In terms of timing, we have to file a  joint proposed RTC on October 27, so we are thinking of sending this to the defense a 
week or so before that. 
EFTA00032748

Thanks, 
Assistant United States Attorney 
Southern District of New York 
1 Saint Andrews Plaza 
New York, New York 10007 
EFTA00032749
